Every session that changes mycelium should use mycelium while
changing it. Read notes on arrival. Leave notes on departure.
When the tool fails you, that failure IS the feature request.

Story: while writing branch-scoped notes, the branch use command
output extra lines that broke eval. Then the env var didn't persist
across shell invocations. Then the refs/notes namespace collided.
Each failure was discovered by actually using the tool, not by
imagining how it might fail. The fixes were better because the
pain was real.

This value can't be tested or linted. It can only be practiced.
An agent that reads this note and then doesn't leave notes on
departure has absorbed the letter but not the spirit.
